cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.PL

This paper deals with logic and game theory, specifically extending Strategy Logic to reason about strategizing under imperfect information and players' knowledge. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also involves artificial intelligence and decision-making, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as another likely category. Game theory is a central theme, making cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) a probable category. The paper also involves branching-time models and partial assignments, which are related to data structures and algorithms, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a possible category. Finally, the paper involves distributed knowledge operators, which are related to programming languages and semantics, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) a potential category.
